{"title": "Stimulus-dependent changes of extracellular glucose in the rat hippocampus determined by in vivo microdialysis", "url": "https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0031938409002753", "author": "A Rex and B Bert and H Fink and JP Voigt", "abstract": "Neuronal activity is tightly coupled with brain energy metabolism; and glucose is an important energy substrate for neurons. The present in vivo microdialysis study was aimed at investigating changes in extracellular glucose concentrations in the rat ventral hippocampus \u2026"}